commits.message: Always seek old commits for a repo until we get no more next pages, then set the weHaveTheOldestCommit flag on the repo. Once we have that flag, always get newer commits. Move query date clause builder into getCommitQuery.

Merge pull request #1 from jimkang/untangle

Untangle
Rename getUserGithubCommits to getUserCommits. Correct test targets.
Added tests for getting user commits bound by dates in existing commits.
Update getCommitsForRepos to only include an `until` clause because the API does not respect both `since` and `until`. Get values from `until` from the commits in the given existing repos.
Broke getCommitForRepos out into its own module. Everything outside of is broken, mid-refactor.
Add filtering and sorting of repos by recency.
Quit after hitting rate limit. Emit non-fatal errors, but do not stop the gets.
Some sort of commit collection implementation. Can't tell if it works until my API rate limit lifts.
Shrunk query loads to meet the max complexity and rate limits.
Implement getting commits from GitHub. Getting repos works, getting commits is a problem.

name: namedlevels-api
description: Serves randomly generated old-school 1st Edition AD&D-style classes that have named levels.

commits.message: Use random class if no class is specified.
Stop using multilevel-cache-tools. Reimplement getCachedNamedLevelClass with simple leveldb.
Updated cache client to respond to RPC disconnect.
Switched to psy for cache server. Updated to run cache locally.
Switching to psy for server process supervision.
Turned caching back on. Finding parts of speech for words related to things like 'cohesiveness' can take 10 seconds.
Updated to non-throwing version of levelnamer.
Cast seed to lowercase for consistency.
Switched from change-case to titlecase to support periods in class names.
Updated to use global pm2. Removed start-level-cache as dependency of start.
Update to less flat way of determining how many start HD a class has.
Used probability table for HD type instead of a flat roll.
Added gainsHDForever to the class profile.
Updated to a multilevel-cache-tools version that doesn't log.
Update to return plural form of class name.
Added CORS middleware to accept cross-origin requests.

- Updated server to use memoized getNamedLevelsClass.
- Added deployment targets to Makefile.

name: smidgeodice
description: A bot that will roll dice for you.

commits.message: Switch to service-based process management. Move servers.
Fixed bug with webhook-server interpreting Slack user id references as potential dice strings.
Updated to not respond to self and avoid infinite loop.
Got rid of not-understood-responding so that it can work on a channel without needing a keyword trigger.
Fixed webhook reply to respond with JSON as Slack expects. Added handling for parse failure and unauthorized requests.
Whoops. Rolled back --watch stuff. Didn't do what I thought it did.
Handle reporting rolls with 0 faces. Do not default to d20. Closes #1.
Updated answerTweet to not reply to tweets it's not mentioned in to address #1.
Updated to not reply to retweets at all.
Updated answertweet to set in_reply_to_status_id in its tweets.
Updated server to use custom dividerpicker for answerTweet.
Updated `rollstotweets` to take a function that provides the dice roll => result divider string instead of using a fixed string.
Added a bunch of server config stuff.
Using ' ⇒ ' instead of ': ' to separate roll sources and results.
Updated to separate rolls from stamp with linebreak instead of space for clarity and visual balance.
Switched to separating results with linebreaks instead of commas and spaces. Cut out "breaking apart and putting back together" junk in `rollsToTweets`.
Updated dicecup to version that always returns an array, added ridiculous request test to replytests.
Stopped logging that it is not replying to its own tweets.
Updated to use source from `dicecup.roll` to include sources (e.g. '3d6') along with the results in tweets. Whew.

- Updated `rollstotweets` to add a unique-ish one-char stamp to every tweet so that it can reply with the same answer multiple times.
- Updated `answertweet` to strip mentions from the text so it doesn't roll for people's usernames.
- Added `emojisource` as the provider for the one-char stamps.

- Dropping roll details from tweet for now.
- Breaking tweets on words instead of at the nth character.
Added support for reporting roll errors.

- Implemented posting in answertweet, updated tests.
- Changed rollsToTweets formatting to exclude colons.

- Added some answertweet implementation.
- Added rollsToTweets tests.

commits.message: Convert all caps topics to lowercase.
Pick in a way that still favors the nearest neighbor, but not so sharply. Don't pick works that are just the plural of the transformee.'
Use numbers instead of strings for the neverUnfollow list.
Throttle down the back-and-forth for a bit.
Make a chance that they don't always reply to each other. Be more liberal with replies to normal people.
Separate limits for transform bots and other users.
Set a limit to the number of times a topic can be used for a user.
Add tests missed in previous commit.
Do not pick the message parts of other bots' tweets.
Limit to three replies per five minutes.
Fix waiting period (times less than an hour were getting rounded down) and reduce it to 20 seconds.
Pick rarest word instead of a random word.
Don't pick neighbors that contain the transformee.
Allow PROJECTNAME to be set by environment variable.

name: godtributes
description: Bot that makes demands for gods appropriately.

commits.message: Go back to using original mstranslator since it has updates for MS text translation service changes (uses api_key, is part of Azure now, I guess).
Support picking randomly from override topics.
Add getW2VNeighbors which was missing from git! Also support topic overrides from command in make tribute.
Use id_str instead of id to chronicle replies. ids have become too big!
Do not reply to tweets mentioning fascism for now to avoid #38.
Trump has reached national tragedy level. Fuck.
Move get-w2v-neighbors into its own module.
Don't use w2v neighbors when using vision. Stop saying 'fatter wallet'. Add support for dry run mode in exhortationserver.
For now, always use one of the nouns from the tweet in addition to neighbors instead of just all neighbors.
Use word2vec in unprompted tributes sometimes.
Avoid proper nouns from word2vec neighbors by checking for uppercase.
Allow only phrases ending in nouns and NOT starting with verbs in w2v results.
Filter out phrases that are dumb.

Merge pull request #37 from jimkang/gn

 Gn
Work w2v neighbors into exhortations. Bring back actual tweeting in exhortationserver. Update iscool and can-i-chime-in.
Update nounfinder to quieter version. Remove iscool as direct dependency, as it is used through nounfinder and can-i-chime-in.
Add module to get suitable nouns from w2v nearest neighbors.
Fix translation tests. Make their output easier to read.
Turn down upper end of max commonness for image topic. Turn on vision.
Add vision donor; turn off vision for rest of month.
Add patrons. Fix secondary topic pool for general thanks to vision stuff.
Drop donor stuff to make tributes a little more focused.
Add general public thanks for vision donors.
Shut off vision for rest of month.
Update filtered-followback to version not tripped up by deleted accounts.
Turn down image analysis frequency. Add to false positives.
Turn vision back on for June.
Move servers again. Switch to rsync for deployment.
Set correct user and group for service.

Stop using word lookup caching. Stop using RPC service for chronicler. Stop updating chronicler in maketributes.js. Use systemd service instead of psy to manage process. Log to stdout instead of via bunyan-syslog and let systemd route it to rsyslog. Operate via a single process now. Remove all dependencies that don’t build in Node 6. All tests pass.
Make image analysis switchable via behavior settings.
Update to can-i-chime-in that notices more bad times tweets.
Factored tweetanalyizer out to can-i-chime-in module.
Update filtered-followback to get rid of 1500 -follower spam check limit.
Update filtered-followback to fix problem with only looking at latest 5000 followers.
Loosen up text noun selection slightly; tighten up image noun selection.
Fix bug where image maxCommonness is used for everything by passing whether image is used instead of using variable in (wrong) outer scope.
Adjust maxCommonness only if we're sure we're using an image.
Run image analysis only half the time.
Added more image things not interesting enough to bother with.
Weed out false positives from image analysis API.
Factor mock utils out of exhort-tests.
Factor meat of what-is-image-at-url out into get-image-analysis. Upgrade standard-bail.
Updated filtered-followback to less rate-limit-prone version. Added what-is-up-with-rate-limiting tool.
Forget linebreaks; they don't show in rsyslog anyway.
Pull out time from exhort error (syslog timestamp good enough for most cases). Make log entry more readable with line breaks.
Remove text from exhorter errors in most cases. Add timestamp.
Yo-yo back to fancy log formatting.
Pass logger object to createWordnok that fits existing expectations.
Log user facility instead of local0.
Reordered post-receive dependencies so that everything is shut down during , so that hopefully, we can avoid running out of memory.
Updated to Node v0.12-compatible basicset-chronicler. Updated test to match current MSTranslator result.
Updated to working version of filtered-followback.
Updated mutualize-follower-list to pass a blacklist to filteredFollowback (to reduce the number of API calls) and to use filteredFollowback's callback to update the blacklist.
Refactored mutualize-follower-list to use filtered-followback instead of quidprofollow and twitterjerkdetector.
Updated nounfinder to version that passes onDisconnect responder through to wordnok and multilevel-cache-tools. Added responder that just quits the process.
Updated to log screen_name instead of user id in 'errors'. Updated translation test values.
Updated chroniclerClient to reestablish connection and RPC stream when client is disconnected.
Fixed echo command. By actually putting 'echo' in there.
Updated to not consider a psy op a failure if it returns a non-zero return code.
Updated to use psy to supervise chronicler and exhortations processes.
Updated figures. Inflated existing possibilities by two.
Updated to a fork of mstranslator that reports ArgumentOutOfRangeException. Added a check to see if the tweet is in a translator-friendly language before translating.
Using tweet's lang property instead of languagedetector. Adoy!

Updated exhorter to take probable as an opt and replaced _.sample with probable.shuffle so that test results are consistent. Brought back confidence floor for language detection to avoid false positives, but made it lower than before.
Dropped insistence on 0.5 confidence level for detecting a language. Added Spanish and French tests.
Made random non-English reply much rarer.
Added support for replying in tweet's language.

Merge branch 'master' of github.com:jimkang/godtributes

* 'master' of github.com:jimkang/godtributes:
  Added tribute figures.
Updated twit in hopes that mysterious stream-dry-ups stop.
Updated nounfinder to version that doesn't crash on unexpected partsOfSpeech elements.
Whoops. Rolled back --watch stuff. Didn't do what I thought it did.
Updated to just use the global pm2.
Make exhortation server target depend on chronicler.
Start servers with watch and reload set.
Wait for tweet to post before exiting process.
Refactored maketribute.js to unnest. Added secondary demand support via Wordnik relatedWords.
Added level-cache dependency to tribute target.
Updated start-* make targets so that they don't fail when those processes are already started.
Updated wordnok, nounfinder. Updated nounfinder to use the memoized cache server.
Updated basicset-chronicler to a version that works on Snow Leopard with a 32-bit processor.
Replaced followback and prune with mutualize-follower-list/quidprofollow.
Removed blacklists to avoid confusion. (Was already mostly using `iscool`'s blacklists.)
Updated to `iscool` version with @knowtheory's suggested changes: https://github.com/jimkang/godtributes/pull/32/files
Updated packages, mainly for the iscool 1.0.2.
Moved nounfinder and emojisource out into their own packages.
Extracted wordniksource to its own module, wordnok.
Replaced local iscool module with iscool npm package.
Updated exhorter to not respond to own tweets.
Trying out 'dome' and 'dragon' as figures, to close #26 and #31.
Added logrotate config. (Needs to be manually installed.)
Varied the delay until an exhortation is posted instead of always responding immediately.
Added exhortation server shutdown and startup to post-receive hook target.
Updated replyDateWasNotTooRecent in exhorter to convert date strings to dates before doing calculations.
Updated getExhortationForTweet to pass back the topics used.
Updated exhortationserver to tweet and to record that what it has tweeted about.
Updated checkThatTweetWasNotRepliedTo to handle that chronicler.tweetWasRepliedTo returns an error when it can't find a key for the tweet.
Updated callback signature in exhort tests.
Updated exhorter to bail if there's not enough nouns after filtering.
Implemented filtering if tweet has already been replied to.
Added chroniclerclient (to wrap multilevel stuff), and updated maketribute to use it.
Fixed stop-chronicler target so that it doesn't stop the post-receive target if there's nothing to stop.

- Added start-chronicler.
- Updated makefile to handle post-receive stuff.
- Cleaned up package.json.
Added 'chokehold' and 'coroner' to tragedy blacklist and 'holocaust' to regular blacklist to fix #24 and #25.
Updated blacklist so that 'transgender' is not considered a noun. Fixes #18.

- Added ‘ala’ to false positives to catch “alas.” Fixed #17.
- DRYed up noun cache expected results.
- Fixed iscool tests.
Added ‘ama’ to false positives to address #13.
Fixed canonicalization bugs with passersby and corgis (#14 and #15).
Fixed nounfinder bug in which repeat emoji get counted as nouns multiple times.
Updated emoji parsing to be able to handle emoji on the character level, so that emoji don’t have to be space-separated to be picked up.
Hide some of the logging behind a flag.
Fixed require reference with wrong case (which only works on Mac).
Updated install-cron to append to existing cron instead of replacing it.
Updated cron cmds to cd to a working dir first, then run from there.
Updated exhort to call makeDemandForTopic with emoji opts set, if topic is emoji. Updated noun finder to always count emoji as nouns and approved emoji as interesting nouns.
Added emoji support (#3). tributedemander now has a chance of using an emoji as the topic.
Specified singular form of ‘microwaves’ so that godtributes doesn’t think that it’s ‘microwafe’. Fixes #5.
Added singular-to-plural pass to go after plural-to-singular pass so that we end up with the correct plural, even if the source plural was wrong. Fixes #7.
Added nounfinder test that includes ‘tl;dr’ to cover bug #6, which isn’t currently happening.
Added test for `pls` false positive. Fixed listing which had the ‘plural form’. Fixes #8.
Fixed Mars (with capital M) pluralization bug. (#9)
Updated endsWith to handle empty strings.
Updated topicpool-tests to cite errors when an error assertion fails.

- Dropped reversion of pluralization clause in canonicalized for numerals. It’s fine if it’s a numeral; the client does not have to use it.
- Added noun finder tests for cardinal number words (it should ignore them).
- Removed cardinal number words from uncountables – they are countable, just not something we want to use.
- Updated nounfinder to filter words that are one character and words that are numerals or cardinal number words.

All tests pass again.
Added (failing) test cases for weird plurals.
Added (failing) tests for excluding numbers as nouns.
Added more false positives (iOS, pls, imo) and tests for them.
Added uncountablesuffixes list for canonicalizer to check for endings like ‘-ization’.
Updated exhort.js to use tweetAnalyzer to filter.
Added handling for more tricky pluralization issues.
Added to the set of symbols that can break up words.
Added ‘rt’ to the list of false positives.
Extended time limit for topicpool tests. Wordnik doesn’t always get back in 2000 ms.
Added tweetAnalyzer and tests. Added ferguson to tragedy blacklist.
Added tests for isCool meta-filter. Updated it (and the blacklists) to be case-insensitive.
Updated schedule to exhort only every other hour to avoid running into Twitter rate limit.
Bumped down upper range of max commonnness.
Updated followback to log in logger instead of console.
Added canonical oddities and uncountable nouns.
Added more plural oddities. Moved the handling of ‘pi’ to canonicaloddities because listing it in uncountablenouns caused everything ending in -pi to be considered uncountable.
Added abbr.js to handle expanding abbreviations that should be expanded. Updated canonicalized to use it.
Added canonicaloddities to handle singularizing/pluralizing stuff that just can’t be described by rules.
Stopped pluralizing numerals, iOS, and ALA to address issue #1.
Added wordfilter to filter out additional uncool words.

Updated tweetRepliesToStatuses to drop restriction on replying to replies to self but added filter on noun groups to also eliminate topics used in tributes (in addition to existing filter for topics already used to reply to user).
Updated record/topicWasUsedInTribute to save and search using singular forms.
Updated recordkeeper.recordThatTopicWasUsedInTribute and topicWasUsedInTribute to normalize to lowercase.
Updated maketribute.js to record use of topic.
Added topicWasUsedInTribute and recordThatTopicWasUsedInTribute to recordkeeper.
Added missing file from last commit.
Added checks for valid JSON strings before parsing and risking an exception.
Added support for both --simulate and —onlytestsubject switches at the same time.
Fixed bug reference to maxCommonnessForTopic which was causing everything to always be filtered all the time. Added log for when it filtered everything.
Added log for maxCommonness. Bumped “lower” bound for maxCommonness to 20 (which should filter less stuff).
Made maxCommonnessForReplyTopic into a range. Updated exhort.js to randomly pick a number from that range to determine max commonness.
Fixed messed up regex which was preventing noun finding.
Rolled back useCanonical=true change because it eliminated some nouns like ‘feed’.
Added more punctuation to strip from nouns.
Added prepphrasepicker in place of static ‘FOR THE’.

- Switched to using the useCanonical flag with Wordnik.
- Factored blacklist check out into iscool.js.
- Added tragedyHappenedRecently flag to behaviorsettings.
- Added false positives list.
Factored handleTwitterError out into its own module.
Added prune.js, which unfollows followers that aren’t following @godtributes.
Updated getNounsFromText to use the blacklist.
Renamed minimumInterestingnessForReplyTopic to maximumCommonnnessForReplyTopic to be less confusing. Tweaked values.
Updated exhort’s target tweet filtering to exclude replies to self rather than all replies.
Lengthened time between replies. Added to blacklist.

Log readability changes.

- Updated logger.log to log topic as string, and the rest in a formatted string in a payload object.
- Updated logger to support turning off Rollbar in simulation mode.
Fixed logic in checkIfNounsWereUsed. Previously, when the used flags were all false, it would stop the tweet, which is wrong. We want to do that when *any* of them are true, rather.
Added followback.js to follow back those that follow @godtributes.

- Fixed bug in which recordThatTopicWasUsedInReplyToUser used a different id format from topicWasUsedInReplyToUser. Fixed logic mistake in topicWasUsedInReplyToUser.
- Added record keeper tests.
Updated the number of hours to wait between exhortations.
Updated tributemaker's initial log to use logger.
Added required id for topic-user object.

- Added recordThatTopicWasUsedInReplyToUser and topicWasUsedInReplyToUser to record keeper.
- Added checks for nouns already used per user to replyIfTheresEnoughUsers.
Limited attempts to reply to two per run, per user.
Fixed bug: It was replying to the same user if they had been replied to in LESS than 12 hours rather than MORE.

- Renamed —-onlyme to —-onlytestsubject. Updated exhort to check for that first and skip the followers/ids call.
- Added behaviorsettings.js.
Fixed problem with replies not being connected to original tweet by using id_str instead of id in in_reply_to_status_id in update POST.
Updated exhort to handle not being able to get statuses for an update. Extended the waiting period for tweeting at a user.
Added exhort jobs to the cron.
Updated exhort to really post tweets. Fixed exhortIfNotTooSoon logic - error means that person has never been replied at.

Added recordkeeper to track in a LevelDB database which tweets were already replied to and when users were last replied to. Updated exhort to use it to not tweet users that have been replied to in the last 8 hours and to not reply to tweets that it has already replied to.

- Implemented exhortation assembly in exhort.replyToStatusWithNouns.
- Updated replyIfTheresEnoughMaterial in exhort to base reply likelihood on the number of relevant nouns found.
- Moved figure picking from maketribute to figurepicker.js.
- Updated nounfinder.isWorthCheckingForNounHood to exclude single-letter words.
- Updated getWordFrequency error log to include word that triggered empty response body.

- Added alternate tribute figure opt to makeDemandForTopic.
- Added —-simulate switch to maketribute.js.
- Updated maketribute to sometimes use alternate tribute figures.

- Moved noun-related stuff from exhort.js to nounfinder/nounfinder-tests and added caching, singularization, other fixes.
- Moved singularization/pluralization stuff from tribute demander to canonicalizer.
- Updated getPartOfSpeech to return all of the parts of speech the given word could be. Renamed it to getPartsOfSpeech. Renamed original getPartsOfSpeech to getPartsOfSpeechForMultipleWords.

- Filtered statuses for “interesting” nouns via Wordnik frequencies, used number of interesting nouns to decide whether to reply to a status.
- Added filtering of numeral words like “3”.
- Added more conditions for detecting an RT of self.
- Got rid of infinite loop (inner `done` was calling itself).
- Refactored.
Added filterNounsForInterestingness, which uses frequency counts of words to determine whether they’re interesting, to exhort.js.
Added getWordFrequency and getWordFrequencies to wordniksource. Factored runOperationOverWords out of getPartsOfSpeech.
Updated tributedemander to handle singular topics ending in -us.
Started exhort.js. Just picks nouns from follwers’ tweets for now.
Added URI encoding to getPartOfSpeech call. Added apostrophe test.
Added special handling for words ending with 'is'. Factored topicsTest out of the tests.
Updated maketribute to just post once and let an outside process handle scheduling.
Updated tributedemander to check for gerunds before trying to pluralize.
Updated “-ness” to uncountable nouns to avoid “SOURNESSES FOR THE SOURNESS GOD”.
Updated botgod (now named maketribute) to get topic and then make a demand for it and tweet it.

commits.message: Do not prefix filePath with / if htmlDir is empty.
Update callbacks for githubFile.update due to its cb signature change.
Delay between each cell json file update.
Delay before updating video metadata to give GitHub sync time.
Use previous indexes, not current indexes, in previous index links.
Put previous indexes where they are visible.
Generate previous index page(s) links at bottom of index pages.
Add delays in add cells transform to make sure it more rarely updates a file in git with an old commit (and fails).
Fix metaDir for page info metadata.
Add single video page transform implemented. Currently getting a 'sha wasn't supplied' error when running service.
Add test for adding single video page in git.
Update makeIndexHTMLFromPageSpec to sort in reverse chronological order.

Convert addCellsToPagesInGit to a transform function, since page updates need to happen every time a single cell is added, not just at the end of the stream. Fix html fragment stream by having videoTweetToBuffer add the `videoFilename` instead of bufferToGit.
Implement adding cells to pages of cells.
Factor encoders out into own module.
Start thinking of stream contents as cells that can be changed, sort of like stem cells.
Streaming from Twitter to git is working!
Post metadata via bufferToGit and implement thing that pulls from timeline to push to the stream.
Support setting the location in git where the files go.
Fix tweet to buffer tests to use correct URLs.
Added tests for buffer to git.
Video tweets to buffer stream is working.

commits.message: Take file sha and pass back content object instead of commit object, since the content sha is what you need to do updates on that file.
Update  to pass commit with sha.
Support specifying a parentSha in  so that it can skip retrieving the file before committing an update.
Include file path in update error.
Strip newlines from base64 to be decoded so there's no problems on Mobile Safari.

name: lampbearer

commits.message: Rumors are a bit noisy (and out-of-date at this point). Stop rendering.
Fix party reset and make sure link selections tick works on are always correct so no crashes happen while moving.
Longer callouts. Move view to the right a bit. Add exit mutualization code.
Interpolate from red to blue to display elevation via spot borders.
Indicate elevation via brightness. Separte spots a little more.
Fix misformatting of fields with linebreaks added during edits by rendering as html. Make spot id editable.
Update getPropertySafely to handle the object itself being undefined. Add support for resetting party positions. Add save button on bottom, too.
Merge branch 'gh-pages' of github.com:jimkang/lampbearer into gh-pages
Get and update data in a different repo. Preserve line breaks in editable fields by saving the html.
Merge branch 'gh-pages' of github.com:jimkang/lampbearer into gh-pages
Make names, descriptions, and instructions editable.
Add missing files. Update to the github-file version that works on Mobile Safari.
Render parties as dots. Define default values for missing route entries.
More adventure. Render sheets for monsters.
THAC0 calculation; render vitals. Hide/show some sections.
Implemented rendering for sheet sections. And more!
Added spots, character generation stuff. Tuned graph forces for fewer link crossings.
Print yaml for update party state.
Make sure allParties is passed when rendering after filtering spots.
Make sure party gets removed from spot when they leave it. Indicate party at spot by darkening circle.
Added rerendering after moving parties. Temporarily stopped dragging.
Render instructions. Added a few more spots.
Get things to not be on top of each other.
Add placeholder spots. Make nodes repel each other more.
Set different border colors for nodes.
Renaming currently existing 'things' to spots. There will later be other types of things.
Filter boxes to the one corresponding to the node clicked in the graph.
